<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 7:20PM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Oakland
and northern Macomb Counties through 800 PM EDT...
At 720 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Romeo, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds around 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could damage unsecured objects.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Romeo around 735 PM EDT.
Armada around 750 PM EDT.
Richmond and Memphis around 800 PM EDT.
Other locations impacted by this storm include New Haven, Lakeville,
Stoney Creek Metro Park, Leonard, Ray Center, Washington and
Rochester Hills.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
